headline.main: Later from Havana--Arrival out of Hon. W. R. King, in Improved Health--Marine Disasters at Key West, &c.

docs.lead_paragraph: The steamship Isabel, Capt. ROLLIN, from Havana the 8th inst., and Key West the morning of the 9th, has arrived at this port. The U. S. steamship Fulton, with Hon. W. R. KING on board, arrived at Havana on the 6th inst. Mr. KING was in improved health.

docs.lead_paragraph: This Texas of ours is an astonishing prolific country. Every field stands luxuriant, crowded, so that it can scarce wave under the breeze, with corn or sugar, or wheat or cotton. Every cabin is full and overflowing, through all its doors and windows, with white haired children.

headline.main: LATEST INTELLIGENCE; By Telegraph to the New-York Daily Times. XXXIId CONGRESS...Second Session SENATE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES. NEW-YORK STATE LEGISLATURE. ASSEMBLY

docs.lead_paragraph: The CHAIR laid before the Senate a copy of the laws and resolutions passed in the Territory of Oregon. Messrs, CASE and UNDERWOOD presented memorials in favor of securing to American citizens abroad religious worship.
